HANTAVIRUS PULMONARY SYNDROME - CANADA: UPDATE JAN 19
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Hantavirus pulmonary syndrome - USA: Update Jan 14 980118155105
Date: Tue, 20 Jan 1998 17:29:07 -0500
From: Harvey Artsob <Harvey_Artsob@hc-sc.gc.ca>

Following is a summary of confirmed cases of hantavirus pulmonary syndrome
(HPS) reported in Canada as of January 19,1998:
Number of cases: 24
Province: Alberta - 15
British Columbia - 6
Saskatchewan - 3
NOTE: One case from Saskatchewan may have been exposed in Saskatchewan or
British Columbia; data still pending.
Sex: Male - 16 (66.7%)
Female - 8 (33.3%)
Age: Mean - 40.5 years (16-62)
Outcome: 7 died (29.9%)
Year: 1989 - 1
1990 - 1
1992 - 1
1994 - 8
1995 - 3
1996 - 3
1997 - 6
1998 - 1
All confirmed cases of HPS have occurred in Canada's 3 western provinces.
One suspect case from the province of Ontario discussed previously on
ProMED-mail could not be confirmed as a case of HPS.
--
Denise Werker
Epidemiologist
Bureau of Field Epidemiology and Surveillance
Health Canada
e-mail: Denise_Werker@hc-sc.gc.ca
